   (NYT23) HARTFORD, Conn. -- Aug. 22, 1999 -- CT-PROMISE-KEEPERS,
8-22 -- A prayer opens a conference held Friday and Saturday in the
Hartford Civic Center Coliseum by Promise Keepers, an evangelical
Christian ministry. The group is trying to increase attendance at
its rallies. More than 12,000 men had packed into the basketball
arena for the rally. The group has largely faded from public view
since its ``Stand in the Gap'' rally drew hundreds of thousands of
men to the National Mall in Washington in 1997. The group has
shrunk but is still huge, with 180 full-time employees and annual
revenues of $41 million. (George Ruhe/New York Times Photo)
</P>
