Toms River plays Boise, Idaho, on Monday night. (Chang W. Lee/New
York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT20) SPARKS, Nev. -- Aug. 22, 1999 -- TAILHOOK-CONVENTION,
8-22 -- The Tailhook convention, site of sexual misconduct that
shook the Navy in 1991, is now a much different kind of event, is
now a much calmer event. Pamela Salisbury, left, was one of the few
women this weekend at the aviators' gathering in Sparks this
weekend. Comdr. Chuck Wright, says the gathering convention was ``a
lot more subdued.'' (Don Preisler/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT19) ALEXANDRIA, Va. -- Aug. 22, 1999 -- DIVALL-PROFILE, 8-22
-- Linda DiVall, Elizabeth Dole's pollster at her office in
Alexandria. After Ms. DiVall was hired to work on Mrs. Dole's bid
for the Republican presidential nomination earlier this year, a few
Republicans contacted the campaign to protest the decision. ``They
didn't think I was conservative enough,'' says Ms. DiVall. The
criticism, Ms. DiVall said, ignored her work in the past for
politicians well to the right of Mrs. Dole -- former House Speaker
Newt Gingrich sprang quickly to mind. (Shana Raab/New York Times
Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT19) PORT ISABEL, Texas -- Aug. 22, 1999 -- GULF-HURRICANE-3,
8-22 --Powerful winds from Hurricane Bret snapped a treetop in Port
Isabel on Sunday, not far from the causeway leading to South Padre
Island. Bret is the first hurricane of the 1999 season and the
first major hurricane to threaten south Texas since Hurricane Allen
caused $55 million in damage in 1980. (Bryce Harper/New York Times
Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT18) RAYMONDVILLE, Texas -- Aug. 22, 1999 --
