The St. Louis Cardinals Mark McGwire hitting his 49th home run of
the year against the New York Mets on Sunday, in the first game of
a double-header. Big Mac launched the monstrous homer, an estimated
502 feet, in the first-inning, and shattered a light bulb on the
scoreboard. Still, the Mets came from five runs down to beat the
Cardinals 8-7 on Edgardo Alfonzo's RBI single in the ninth inning.
(Ozier Muhammad/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   The New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
