have enough water to walk more than seven miles. By Al Casillas,
credit BORDER PATROL SPOKESMAN &QL; 
QUOTE-In World War II, we could make it miserable for whole city
blocks. But things are different now. You have to pinpoint the
threat and attack it precisely. By Jim Parrington, credit MARINE
MAJOR &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
