   RUSSIA-PROSPERITY-GAP (Moscow) _ The August 1998 devaluation of
the ruble dealt a heavy blow to the nation. Russia's economic
reformers were discredited. The capital's fledgling financial
sector was hit by massive layoffs. The purchasing power of Russian
consumers dwindled. By using the particularly Russian talent for
adapting to seemingly any hardship, however, many Russians have
managed to cling to vestiges of their pre-crisis life. By Michael
R. Gordon.
