<HEADLINE>
TEXAS BRACES AS HURRICANE HITS LAND 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (UPDATES with hurricane weakening in 3rd graf, being made a
Category 3 in   10th graf.) (ART ADV: Photo is being sent to NYT photo clients. Graphic and map
are being sent to NYT graphics clients. Non-subscribers may make
individual purchase by calling (888) 603-1036 or (888) 346-9867.) 
(rk) 
 By JIM YARDLEY    
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service      
<TEXT>
<P>
   CORPUS CHRISTI, Texas _ With winds reaching 125 mph and a tidal
surge expected to reach 12 feet, Hurricane Bret rumbled ashore
early Sunday evening along the south Texas coast, hours after tens
of thousands of anxious residents evacuated inland along clogged
highways.
</P>
