</P>
<P>
   More than a foot of rain fell in many areas along the coast, and
the authorities feared that the slow-mov- ing storm could cause
widespread flooding on Monday. By midnight the fastest winds had
dropped to 105 mph as the storm, which had moved 25 miles inland,
slow- ly diminished.
</P>
<P>
   There were no reported injuries, but officials, who remained in
shel- ters, said it was too early to assess real damage.
</P>
