would take a direct hit, Hinojosa said county workers drove buses
to low-lying areas to evacuate residents, most of whom refused to
go.
</P>
<P>
   ``I got the impression there is a lot of complacency,'' he said.
``People didn't think it was going to hit.''
</P>
<P>
   Ms. Moss, the state emergency management official, noted that
this weekend marked the seventh anniversary of Hurricane Andrew.
The most violent recent storm to his Corpus Christi was Celia,
which lashed the coast on Aug. 3, 1970, killing 11 people, causing
tens of millions of dollars in damages and flooding much of the
city's downtown.
</P>
<P>
   Witt noted that two other storms are also forming that could
potentially threaten the East Coast of the United States. ``This
season has just really truly started.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
