<HEADLINE>
WARREN-BEATTY-AS-POWER-BROKER 
 WHY-DENTISTS-STILL-EXIST
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SLATE, the premier online magazine of politics and culture, is
now available to your readers from The New York Times Syndicate.
</P>
<P>
   Today:
</P>
<P>
   1. ACTOR MAY NOT BE PRESIDENTIAL, BUT HE'S A MASTER MANIPULATOR,
by David Plotz
</P>
<P>
   The media snicker at the idea of Warren Beatty as
actor-politician, who presumes to speak on the day's great issues.
But consider Beatty as a self-made businessman and Hollywood power
broker. His sympathizers rightly ask why Steve Forbes, who
inherited his millions, is a serious candidate, while Beatty is a
joke.
</P>
<P>
   1,200 words. Slugged: BC-WARREN-BEATTY-AS-POWER-BROKER-NYTSF
</P>
<P>
   -------
</P>
