   2. IN THE AGE OF FLUORIDE, DENTISTS MANAGE TO FLOURISH, by David
Plotz
</P>
<P>
   The transformation of American dentistry from drill-and-fill to
shoot-and-loot is an unlikely business success story of the '90s, a
case study in how a profession can work itself out of a job and
still prosper.
</P>
<P>
