<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    COX NEWS SERVICE COMMENTARY BUDGET
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   These columns for release Tuesday, August 24, 1999 are moving
today to clients of the New York Times News Service.
</P>
<P>
   All columns have moved, in the commentary (k) category. If you
have questions or need a resend, please call CoxNet, the Cox News
Service, at 404-526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   GEEWAX-Y2K-COLUMN _ Marilyn Geewax's weekly column looking at
issues raised by the coming of 2000. (Geewax, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVED WEDNESDAY.
</P>
<P>
   SCHUETT-COLUMN _ GIBSONBURG, Ohio _ Long before Brando and his
``wild ones'' roared across movie screens, scratching, belching,
and terrorizing small towns, kids growing up in Miami in the late
'40s had an outlaw bunch known as ``The Springs Guys.'' They were
too cool for words. (Schuett, Cox News Service) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   LANE-COLUMN _ DAYTONA BEACH, Fla. _ I exhaled and told myself
how lucky I was. The car had started again with only the slightest
flick of the key. The car was parked in an inch of mud about 5 feet
from the edge of a pine forest, not far from a drainage ditch and
about 15 yards from the road. The road had turned. I had not. In a
sudden, driving rain, the car was frictionlessly suspended on the
road's slick, watery surface and was not responding either to
brakes, the steering wheel or my adamantly delivered suggestions.
It was hydroplaning. (Lane, Daytona Beach News-Journal) MOVED
</P>
