<P>
   DEAD: Autopsies are steadily losing their importance in Kansas,
Missouri and around the country, causing alarm among health care
professionals. They fear that patient care quality and medical
knowledge have been reduced as a result of the decline. The reason
for the decline? Insurance plans aren't paying for them and new
