u v BC-HEARST-NEWS-BUDGET-HN     08-23 0178
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-HEARST-NEWS-BUDGET-HNS </SLUG>
  
 Monday, Aug. 23, 1999     
 Editors     
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Hearst News Service will file the following for Tuesday. If
you have questions, please call Susie McBee or Tim Spence at
202-298-6920.
</P>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON NEWS (``w'' category)
</P>
<P>
   PAN-AM-103-FAMILIES (Washington) _ Families of victims of the
1988 bombing of Pan Am Flight 103 over Lockerbie, Scotland, are
briefed here by Scottish prosecutors about the upcoming trial in
the Netherlands of two Libyans accused of the crime. Attorney
General Janet Reno said last week that the two-day, closed meeting
was being arranged to try to address the families' questions before
the trial begins. By MARK HELM.
</P>
<P>
   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MEANS-COLUMN (Washington) _ Texas Gov. George W. Bush's problem
is that he is is finally being judged by the harsh standards for
personal behavior long applied to President Clinton. The way Bush
has bumbled the cocaine controversy raises questions about whether
he is hypocritical, evasive and arrogant. By MARIANNE MEANS.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-08-23-99 1359EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
