</P>
<P>
   GLOBAL-HOLIDAYS (Undated) _ For the financial services industry,
the emergence of global capitalism has unleashed a new horror:
global holiday schedules. Fortunately, there is Paul Spraos, who,
since 1992, has produced an international holiday calendar, which
heroically attempts to identify all the holidays _ ``bad business
days,'' he calls them _ that will occur in more than 100 countries
over the next 100 years. And next month, Spraos will begin offering
his calendar over the Internet. By Diana B. Henriques.
</P>
<P>
   With photo.
</P>
<P>
   MEL-FARR-CARS (Detroit) _ Mel Farr, who has the nation's largest
black-owned dealership, is expanding his car leasing business,
offering used cars to more customers with no credit. His plan has a
novel twist: the leased cars will be equipped with a device that
prevents the car from being started if the weekly payments have not
been made. By Robyn Meredith.
</P>
