French water utility giants in light of Suez Lyonnaise des Eaux's
announcement Monday that it plans to buy the remaining 67 percent
of United Water Resources of Harrington Park, N.J., it does not
already own for $900 million. By John Tagliabue.
</P>
<P>
   MARKET (New York) _ At 2 p.m. EDT, stocks were higher ahead of
the Federal Reserve meeting on Tuesday. The Dow Jones industrial
average was up 115 points, the S&AMP;P 500 up 13 and the Nasdaq
composite index up 47 points. At midday, the 30-year bond was
yielding 6 percent. European markets were higher, with London up
2.39 percent and Frankfurt up 0.91 percent. In Japan, the Nikkei
closed up 0.75 percent and Hong Kong's Hang Seng index ended up
0.05 percent. By Kenneth N. Gilpin.
