<DOCNO> NYT19990823.0191 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-23 14:17 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A6548 &Cx1f; tdt-z
u e BC-MOVIE-VIDEOS-BOS &LR;      08-23 0442
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-MOVIE-VIDEOS-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
`DREAMLIFE OF ANGELS' IS A MUST-SEE 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS: ``The Dreamlife of Angels'' _ One of the
year's best films. Erick Zonca makes his feature film debut with an
understated French tale of two young women on the edge of town and
the edge of life. It's got fully realized characters, subdued
cinematography, and a realism that seems lost in American film.
Elodie Bouchez and Natacha Regnier are magnificent. This one should
not be missed.
</P>
<P>
   ``Six Ways to Sunday'' _ Be forewarned, this is a very violent
gangster film. But for those who can enter this dark world, it's
quite a trip with Oedipal overtones combined with Judeo-Christian
conflict. Norman Reedus is terrific as a kid from Ohio who goes to
work collecting debts for the Mob. And look for the transcendent
gangsta, Isaac Hayes.
</P>
<P>
   ``Paul Robeson: Here I Stand'' _ One of the greatest singers,
actors, athletes, and linguists of the 20th century got short
shrift in his own country because of his color and his politics.
The only uncontroversial aspect of Robeson's life was his art. This
documentary includes some fine performance footage and an interview
conducted while he was playing Othello on Broadway _ the first
black man to do so.
</P>
<P>
   ``Celebrity'' _ If anyone should know about celebrity, it's
writer-director Woody Allen. But the man about Manhattan doesn't
get much deeper than a People magazine profile in this
disappointing effort. Star Kenneth Branagh impersonates the
neurotic auteur and Donald Trump plays himself. Also, look for
Leonardo DiCaprio playing a young movie star.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS: Aug. 31: ``Titanic'' (DVD), ``Cleopatra,''
``The Very First Jeeves and Wooster,'' ``The Doctor Is In'' (``The
Bob Newhart Show''), ``Idle Hands.'' Sept. 7: ``The Other Sister''
(DVD), ``Mary-Kate and Ashley's Fashion Party,'' ``Deep Crimson,''
``Park City: The Vanguard Collection,'' ``Twin Dragons'' (DVD),
``The Crow: Stairway to Heaven.'' Sept. 14: ``Cookie's Fortune,''
``Children of Heaven,'' ``The Snow of Winter,'' ``The Prince of
Egypt'' (DVD), ``All Creatures Great and Small,'' ``God Said Ha!,''
``Children of Heaven.'' Sept. 21: ``My Favorite Martian,''
``Labyrinth,'' ``Atomic Train,'' ``The Dark Crystal,'' ``Lulu on
the Bridge.'' Sept. 28: ``The Mummy'' (DVD), ``Alvin and the
Chipmunks Meet Frankenstein,'' ``My Favorite Martian'' (DVD). Oct
5: ``Lolita'' (1999 version), ``Scooby-Doo and the Witch's Ghost.''
Oct. 19: ``The Wizard of Oz'' (remastered and DVD). Oct. 31: ``The
Blair Witch Project.''
</P>
</TEXT>
