   DRUGS-CONGRESS (Washington) _ After years of wavering by the
Clinton administration, Congress is close to forcing a major
expansion of economic sanctions against international narcotics
traffickers and the businesses that work with them. By Tim Golden.
</P>
<P>
   SRILANKA-TIRUCHELVAM (Colombo) _ In a country where there is no
vocation more perilous, indeed more radical, that being a voice for
peace, Neelan Tiruchelvam had worked to bring an end to the savage
ethnic conflict that has tormented this lush island nation. Last
month, a suicide bomber blew him up. Special Report. By Celia W.
Dugger.
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON
</P>
<P>
   (Will move in ``w'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   RESEARCH-CONGRESS (Washington) _ Universities teamed up with
lobbyists to obtain nearly $800 million from Congress last year in
obscurely written ``earmarks'' for multimillion-dollar studies in
wood research, papaya fungus, bridge-building, agribusiness and
other academic oddities. Almost all the earmarks were inserted,
without public debate, in closed-door conferences. By Tim Weiner.
</P>
