<P>
   TECH-REPORT _ Tech briefs on new products and developments. This
week: Years ago, when science fiction novels _ not video games _
were an obsession with most boys and some girls, the robot was
king. The robots of science fiction were wonderful (and sometimes
awful) creatures that could think for themselves and that seemed
like mechanical versions of a real person. For a time, it seemed
almost certain that _ as technology moved to the stage where such
things were possible _ robot housekeepers and waiters would be
common by the end of the century. (Husted, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). MOVED.
