u i BC-SPOT-BUDGET-BOS &LR;      08-23 0501
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SPOT-BUDGET-BOS </SLUG>
  
 For Release TUESDAY AMs, August   24, 1999  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Boston Globe plans to move the following stories for use by
NYTimes News Service clients.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; For questions about stories, contact  &UR; Frank Perrotta  &LR; at the
Boston Globe,  &UR; 617-929-2597. &LR;  For individual purchase of graphics
or photos please call 212 556-4204 or -1927.
</P>
<P>
   All stories will bear the BOS designator.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   QUAKE-RESCUE (Aboard the USS Kearsarge) _ Ships from the U.S.
Sixth Fleet arrive, carrying more than 2,000 Marines to give aid
and assistance to quake-devastated Turkey. By Aliza Marcus. 1000
words.
</P>
<P>
   w/
</P>
<P>
   QUAKE-POLITICS (Istanbul) _ Turks, always state-oriented, are
angry that the government has done so little for them. Many are
beginning to think they may not need government so much. By
Jonathan Gorvette. 600 words.
</P>
<P>
   HONKONG-AIRPORT (Hong Kong) _ It was a dramatic crash that
resulted in little loss of life. But now the questions are growing
about Hong Kong's year-old, $20 billion airport. Was it built in
the wrong place? By Indira A.R. Lakshmanan.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   TEXAS-BRET (Harlingen, Texas) _ Hurricane Bret is downgraded to
a tropical storm as it plods across a sparsely populated swath of
southern Texas. By Richard Chacon. 1100 words.
</P>
<P>
   RETIREMENT-COUPLES (Undated) _ Retirement is supposed to be when
husband and wife finally get to enjoy their time together. But a
new study finds that depression and marital conflict can develop,
especially where a spouse continues to work. By Dolores Kong. 800
words.
</P>
