<HEADLINE>


</HEADLINE>
 
(For use by NYTimes News Service clients)  CREAMY CHILI DIP WITH CHIPS
<TEXT>
<P>
   2 packages (8 ounces EACH) cream cheese &QL; 
1 can (15 ounces) chili without beans &QL; 
1 can (4 ounces) diced green chiles &QL; 
3 green onions, chopped
</P>
<P>
   Cut cream cheese into cubes. Combine with chili, chiles and
green onions in a 1 1/2-quart glass casserole. (Ingredients can
also be combined in a 2-quart saucepan and cooked over low heat on
stove top.)
</P>
<P>
   Just before serving time, cook dip, covered with wax paper, in
microwave oven on 50 percent power 8 to 10 minutes, stirring every
2 minutes.
</P>
<P>
   Keep warm or rewarm as necessary. Serve with tortilla chips.
Makes 4 cups, 8 to 10 servings.
</P>
<P>
   From ``The Casual Gourmet, 50 Easy Entertaining Menus'' by
Phillis M. Carey. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
PASTA WITH SUN-DRIED TOMATO &QL; 
AND PINE NUT SAUCE
</P>
<P>
   1 large onion, chopped &QL; 
1 clove garlic, minced &QL; 
1/3 cup olive oil &QL; 
1/3 cup pine nuts &QL; 
8 oil-packed sun-dried tomatoes, chopped &QL; 
1/3 cup unsalted butter &QL; 
Water &QL; 
1 pound fresh fettuccine OR linguine &QL; 
Fresh chopped parsley &QL; 
Black pepper &QL; 
1/3 cup Parmesan cheese
</P>
<P>
   Saute onion and garlic in olive oil with pine nuts until onion
is transparent and pine nuts are toasted. Add tomatoes and toss
lightly. Add butter and let melt slowly.
</P>
<P>
   Meanwhile, bring a large pot of salted water to a boil. Add
pasta and cook to taste, about 3 to 5 minutes. Drain well.
</P>
<P>
   Place pasta on a platter and top with sauce. Toss several times
to combine. Top with parsley, pepper and Parmesan cheese. Serve
immediately. Makes 6 servings.
</P>
<P>
   From ``The Casual Gourmet, 50 Easy Entertaining Menus'' by
Phillis M. Carey. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
PEACHES BAKED WITH &QL; 
AMARETTI AND ALMONDS
</P>
<P>
   6 to 8 medium peaches, cut into thick wedges &QL; 
1/4 cup Amaretto liqueur &QL; 
1/2 cup Amaretti cookie crumbs &QL; 
1/2 cup finely chopped toasted almonds &QL; 
1/4 cup chilled butter &QL; 
Vanilla ice cream
</P>
<P>
   Arrange peaches in a 2-quart flat baking dish. Pour Amaretto
over and toss gently. Let stand 30 minutes.
</P>
<P>
   Combine Amaretti crumbs and almonds in a small bowl. Add butter
and cut in with a pastry fork or fingers until mixture resembles a
coarse meal. Sprinkle over peaches.
</P>
<P>
   Bake in preheated 375-degree oven 15 to 20 minutes, until
peaches are tender and topping browns. Cool slightly.
</P>
<P>
   Serve warm topped with vanilla ice cream. Makes 8 servings.
</P>
<P>
   From ``The Casual Gourmet, 50 Easy Entertaining Menus'' by
Phillis M. Carey. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
LEMON CURD TART
</P>
<P>
   PASTRY: &QL; 
1 1/2 cups flour &QL; 
2 tablespoons granulated sugar &QL; 
Pinch salt &QL; 
1 large egg yolk &QL; 
1/2 cup chilled unsalted butter, cut into 6 pieces &QL; 
4 to 5 tablespoons ice water &QL; 
FILLING: &QL; 
1 cup fresh lemon juice &QL; 
1/4 cup finely minced lemon peel &QL; 
1/2 cup unsalted butter, melted &QL; 
6 eggs &QL; 
1 1/2 cups granulated sugar &QL; 
Powdered sugar for top
</P>
<P>
   For Pastry, place flour, sugar, salt and egg yolk in a food
processor fitted with a metal blade. Pulse until butter is size of
lima beans. With machine running, pour ice water through feed tube.
When dough begins to form a ball, remove and wrap in plastic wrap.
Chill 1 hour before rolling out.
</P>
<P>
   Roll dough out and ease into a lightly buttered 10-inch tart pan
with a removable bottom. Prick bottom and sides with a fork;
refrigerate until ready to bake.
</P>
<P>
   For Filling, combine lemon juice, peel and melted butter in a
medium bowl. Stir in eggs and granulated sugar and mix well. Pour
lemon mixture into chilled crust.
</P>
<P>
   Bake in preheated 400-degree oven about 30 to 40 minutes, until
golden brown. Cool on a rack to room temperature. Sprinkle
generously with powdered sugar before serving. Makes 8 servings.
</P>
<P>
   From ``The Casual Gourmet, 50 Easy Entertaining Menus'' by
Phillis M. Carey. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
