<HEADLINE>
MEET INSTRUCTOR PHILLIS CAREY 
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
(Runs with CASUAL-COOKING)  
By NATALIE HAUGHTON 
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
 
SPOTLIGHT ON ... Phillis Carey 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; Age: &LR;  49.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Profession: &LR;  Cooking teacher, cookbook author and free-lance
writer.  &UR; Hometown: &LR;  Born in Pomona; grew up in La Mirada. Now
resides in Carlsbad.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Food background: &LR;  Self-trained. Carey started cooking in
college as a hobby. She has been teaching cooking classes to home
cooks for more than two decades.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Most popular dish she makes: &LR;  Florentine lasagna rolls. &QL; 
Three f &UR; avorite foods: &LR;  Pasta, chicken and chocolate.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Favorite junk food &LR; : French fries. &QL; 
Foods she hates: Liver and sushi.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Secret food passion: &LR;  ``As much warm dungeness crab with butter
as I can get my hands on,'' said Carey.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Favorite thing to cook and &LR;   &UR; eat: &LR;  Mashed potatoes.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Favorite kitchen gadget: &LR;  Flat round stainless-steel meat
pounder without teeth.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Pet peeve: &LR;  People asking her how to make a dish low fat. ``I'm
not particularly into low fat, but I've learned to offer
suggestions to reduce fat in items before I'm asked,'' said Carey.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Favorite cookbook: &LR;  ``San Francisco a La Carte'' and ``San
Francisco Encore,'' both by the Junior League of San Francisco.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Favorite restaurant: &LR;  Laurel in San Diego.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Ideal vacation: &LR;  Any place she doesn't have to cook.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; What does she do when not cooking?: &LR;  Reads mysteries and other
novels.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Dream job: &LR;  To run a really big cooking school.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Worst kitchen disaster: &LR;  Flambeing a dish during a cooking
class and catching the corner of the cabinet on fire.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; If she could dine with anyone (current or historical) who would
it be?: &LR;  Julia Child.
</P>
</TEXT>
