A6879 &Cx1f; ttx-z
r e BC-POKEMON-MANIA-1200(2T     08-23 0730
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-POKEMON-MANIA-1200(2TAKES)-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SO YOU WANT TO BE A POKE-MOM
</HEADLINE>
 (Accompanied by BC-POKEMON-ESSENTIALS) 
(For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By CATHERINE NEWTON 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Pokemon Summer Training League drew legions of Game
Boy-toting tykes to The Parks mall in Arlington, Texas, last week,
and one of them was my son, Jack. For five hours I looked on,
confused, as Jack watched experts battling in the Cerulean Gym,
ordinary gamers battling in the Prime and Poke Cups, and
day-traders swapping Pokemon trading cards from their three-ring
binders. In five hours, I learned important Pokemon tips _ for
example, an ``Ash hat'' that Jack now wants is going to set me back
$12.99 at Sears.
</P>
<P>
   My 9-year-old is a Poke-maniac, one of the 4 million Americans
who have purchased the Red or Blue version of the mysterious
Japanese game in the past 11 months and has fallen fingers-first
into the fantasy land of ``pocket monsters.''
</P>
<P>
   I'd picked up a little Poke-knowledge myself. There's a little
creature called Pikachu in the game. The game uses up scores of AA
batteries. The TV show is on at 3 p.m. daily. But mostly, I was a
Poke-moron. I couldn't relate to my kid and the Poke-passion that
drove him to log 115 hours and 20 minutes in front of a tiny little
screen. I was losing him to Poke-play.
</P>
<P>
   So, humbly, I sat cross-legged on the floor next to sensei Jack
and asked him to share the secrets.
</P>
<P>
   For confused parents everywhere, I offer excerpts from a
conversation between Mom and the master:
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   AWAKENING
</P>
<P>
   Mom: First things first. What's the point of Pokemon? What do
you have to do to win?
</P>
<P>
   Master Jack: There's two ways you can beat the game. First, you
can beat the Elite 4, which are the best trainers.
</P>
<P>
   Mom: Trainer?
</P>
<P>
   MJ: Someone who catches Pokemon with something called a
Pokeball, a Safari Ball, a Great Ball ...
</P>
<P>
   Mom: (writing furiously) Wait, what? What's a Pokeball _ a
Safari Ball?
</P>
<P>
   MJ: (patronizingly) No, Mom. That's Pokeball _ comma _ Safari
Ball _ comma _ Great Ball.
</P>
<P>
   Mom: Oh. Sorry. So that's the first thing _ beat the Elite 4?
</P>
<P>
   MJ: No. That's at the end. That's how you become a master.
Remember you asked me how to win? Another way is to capture all of
the Pokemon, and there are 152 _ but actually, there are 157 with
the glitches of the game and stuff.
</P>
<P>
   Mom: The glitches?
</P>
<P>
   MJ: Never mind. You just need to get 150 to be a master also.
And to be an ultimate master, you have to do both.
</P>
<P>
   Mom: What way are you working on now?
</P>
<P>
   MJ: I already beat the Elite 4. And I have 133 Pokemon.
</P>
<P>
   Mom: How did you beat the trainers?
</P>
<P>
   MJ: First you have to have a Pokemon ready. You have it in your
lineup, which is a place attached to you like a belt or something,
and you can carry up to six Pokemon on it.
</P>
<P>
   Mom: And then you ... find the trainers and battle them?
</P>
<P>
   MJ: Yeah, yes, if you find them.
</P>
<P>
   Mom: Um, where are they?
</P>
<P>
   MJ: They're just, like, there. They're just somewhere like you,
kind of just wandering around looking for others also. Some are
just standing there waiting for you.
</P>
<P>
   Mom: Oh.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   QUESTIONING
</P>
<P>
   MJ: The trainers send out a Pokemon or you send out one.
</P>
<P>
   Mom: Send one out?
</P>
<P>
   MJ: With the Pokeball.
</P>
<P>
   Mom: And then the trainer sends back a Pokemon?
</P>
<P>
   MJ: No. And then a Pokemon can know up to four moves.
</P>
<P>
   (Silence.)
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   DEEPENING
</P>
<P>
   Mom: Moves?
</P>
<P>
   MJ: When you catch a Pokemon wild, it already knows some moves.
It has to know at least one. 'Cause it can't know zero.
</P>
<P>
   Mom: (knowing zero) No, I suppose not. How do you teach it more?
</P>
<P>
   MJ: You have to go to a higher level. Which means you have to
get more hit points. Which means you have to kind of beat more
Pokemon. Or have a weak one at the top of your lineup and then
return it, and it gets hit points automatically.
</P>
<P>
   Mom: (!)
</P>
<P>
   Mom again: So let's say you capture your little Pokemon. How do
you get it to the next level?
</P>
<P>
   MJ: You have to raise it.
</P>
<P>
   Mom: Like a child?
</P>
<P>
   MJ: Not really. You have to battle with it. And then it gets
points. And then it can go up to the next level. And if another
Pokemon is at a higher level, then you get more points if you beat
it. 'Cause it's like a weak one, so it gets more points for just
staying alive. Know what I mean?
</P>
<P>
   Mom: (feeling weak) Do you want something to drink?
</P>
<P>
   MORE nn
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   CONFUSED
</P>
<P>
   MJ: When a Pokemon is at a high enough level, it evolves into a
different one. It evolves into an entirely new Pokemon, but it's a
little the same. Kind of.
</P>
<P>
   Mom: Can you give me an example?
</P>
<P>
   MJ: Like Squirtle is a turtle, and he evolves into Wartortle,
which is another kind of turtle.
</P>
<P>
   Mom: (feeling confident) And he has more power?
</P>
<P>
   MJ: Yes, and he has more defense and attacks special on his
moves. Things like that. Each Pokemon has one special move. Like
Bulbasaur's is vine whip.
</P>
<P>
   Mom: (feeling confused) What?
</P>
<P>
   MJ: It hurts the other Pokemon's health. You have 132 healths.
It beats it and makes it go down to zero, then the other Pokemon
faints. No one can ever kill a Pokemon. It just gets weak and then
you can't use it ... until you go to a Pokemon center.
</P>
<P>
   Mom: And that is ...?
</P>
<P>
   MJ: Well, you go to a lady and she heals all your Pokemon.
There's one in every city.
</P>
<P>
   Mom: How do you get from city to city?
</P>
<P>
   MJ: You have to travel on foot. Or you can get a bike voucher
from someone.
</P>
<P>
   Mom: From who?
</P>
<P>
   MJ: From a Pokemon fan club in the Game Boy. There's a guy who's
the leader of it, who gives you a bike voucher and if you go back
to Cerulean City and then you go to the bike shop and you talk to
the guy and he gives you a bike.
</P>
<P>
   Mom: Talk to the guy? What do you mean?
</P>
<P>
   MJ: You go up to him and press A.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   FAINTING
</P>
<P>
   Mom: (looking at the Game Boy screen) Who is Bill? What is
Bill's PC?
</P>
<P>
   MJ: He gives you the Pokemon where you can deposit and withdraw
them. And you have a PC, too. See, Jack's PC? That's where you can
deposit items. And withdraw them.
</P>
<P>
   Mom: What kind of items?
</P>
<P>
   MJ: Well, I'm about to show you that. You have things like the
Super Rod, the Good Rod, which you go fishing with to find Pokemon.
</P>
<P>
   Mom: And you just collect those things as you go along?
</P>
<P>
   MJ: Some people give you them. Some fishers give you them.
</P>
<P>
   Mom: Fishers?
</P>
<P>
   MJ: People who fish a lot.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   BATTLE CRY
</P>
<P>
   Mom: So what can happen to your Pokemon when they battle? They
can be put to sleep? What does that mean?
</P>
<P>
   MJ: It means that there are moves like hypnosis that make it go
to sleep. Or like Blizzard and Ice Beam.
</P>
<P>
   Mom: Where do you get your freeze power?
</P>
<P>
   MJ: M-o-o-o-o-o-m. From the moves.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   SLEEP
</P>
<P>
   Mom: What are the best Pokemon to have?
</P>
<P>
   MJ: The best lineup is Charizard, Articuno, Venusaur, Zapdos,
Mewtwo and Blastoise. You need different types, because some types
are weak against others. Like Charzar is flame, or fire. Fire is
weak against Water. The different types have different moves.
</P>
<P>
   Mom: What's a typical Fire move?
</P>
<P>
   MJ: The best one would be Fire Blast. It's a TM. Like Blizzard.
</P>
<P>
   Mom: Huh?
</P>
<P>
   MJ: Which means you have to get a machine to do it.
</P>
<P>
   Mom: Machine?
</P>
<P>
   MJ: Sometimes one of the gym leaders gives you a Fire Blast when
you beat him.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   GAME OVER
</P>
<P>
   MJ: (setting up playing cards) Mom, do you want to know about
the cards now? How to battle with the cards?
</P>
<P>
   Mom: Are they like the game?
</P>
<P>
   MJ: Kind of.
</P>
<P>
   Mom: Let's watch a video.
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) &QL; 
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
