Microsoft's first foray into the rarefied dictionary market promise
a mighty international reference guide for the English-speaking
world _ the ``first dictionary born in the information age.'' But
the Encarta World English Dictionary, has also ignited a tart war
of words in the elite universe of dictionary publishing, a
high-volume, low-margin business that suddenly finds itself warily
facing the threat of Microsoft's financial resources, marketing
muscle and global reach. By Doreen Carvajal.
</P>
<P>
   SCI-MUMMIES (Undated) _ Archaeologists unveil a startling trove
of Roman era mummies found recently near Cairo. By John Noble
Wilford. 1,250 words. (MOVED)
</P>
