<HEADLINE>
SIX ESSENTIALS FOR POKEMON TRAINERS
</HEADLINE>
 
(Accompanies BC-PIKEMON-MANIA) (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) By ``MASTER'' JACK
NEWTON 
c.1999 Special to the Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   So your mom won't buy you all the Pokemon stuff you want. Here's
what's best:
</P>
<P>
   1. Game Boy Color and either the Red or the Blue game pak. Red
and Blue are the same game, except that Red has some Pokemon that
Blue doesn't and Blue has some that Red doesn't.
</P>
<P>
   Game Boy Color: $69.99 at Toys R Us
</P>
<P>
   Red or Blue game pak: $29.99 at Toys R Us
</P>
<P>
   2. Game link cables. You need these to battle other people or to
trade Pokemon with other people. Like if your friend has one of the
ones that's only on Blue and you have the Red.
</P>
<P>
   Game link cables: $9.99 at Toys R Us
</P>
<P>
   3. Pokemon Yellow. This game is coming out soon in English, but
I got this one from Japan so it's in Japanese. It's exactly like
Red, except there are a few more trainers. I don't know their
names, but I know what they look like, so I just say, ``Oh, it's a
cool trainer'' or something like that.
</P>
<P>
   Pokemon Yellow: Due next month
</P>
<P>
   4. Trading cards with coins. Alakazam is rare. More rare than
Charizard. The best way to keep your cards is in three-ring binders
with those clear pocket sheets.
</P>
<P>
   Booster card set: $2.99 at Target
</P>
<P>
   5. Pokemon Trainer's Survival Guide. This is for your mom.
You'll already know everything once you start playing.
</P>
<P>
   Sandwich Islands Publishing: $11.95
</P>
<P>
   6. The Pokemon videos. There are 10 of these. They don't really
help you on the game that much, but they're fun. The best is
``Thunder Shock,'' I think. It's Ash vs. a gym leader, and he has
Pikachu's evolved form and it's really hard for Pikachu. You know
Pikachu is Ash's first Pokemon. And he's an electric rodent. He's
not very powerful. He's just the cutest.
</P>
<P>
   Videos: $14.98. At video stores and through Amazon.com.
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) &QL; 
nn
