<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-NC-SCHOOLDESEG-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Possible busing halt has NAACP, parents waiting for judge's
decision
 &HT;    By Chris Burritt
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   CHARLOTTE, N.C. _ In the city that pioneered busing as a tool
for school desegregation, some of Charlotte-Mecklenburg's public
schools could again become segregated if a federal judge allows the
district to end busing, officials said Monday.
</P>
