<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR TUESDAY, AUGUST 24
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Tuesday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-MAGAZINE-MERGER-NYT (moved on Thursday, Aug. 19) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Thursday, Aug. 19,
about the sale of Fairchild Publications to Conde Nast Publications
included an outdated reference to the sale price of The San
Francisco Chronicle, which was bought by the Hearst Corporation,
another suitor for Fairchild. Although no price has been officially
disclosed, a person close to the deal estimates it at $660 million;
$500 million was an earlier estimate by industry analysts.
</P>
