<P>
   ATTENTION EDITORS: The following photos are part of tonight's
New York Times Photo Package, moving Monday, 08/23/99. Photo
clients will automatically receive these photos via AP's
PhotoExpress or may download them from either the Wieck Photo
Database in Dallas at 972-392-0888 or from NYTPhotos on Newscom at
305-448-8411. Non-clients can make individual purchases by calling
(888) 603-1036 or 212-556-4204.
</P>
<P>
   (NYT26) WASHINGTON -- Aug. 23, 1999 -- GORE-PROTEST-FLOATER,
08-23 -- Uniformed Secret Service agents arrest members of the
group called ``AIDS Drugs for Africa'' during a demonstration
outside the Old Executive Office Building in Washington on Monday.
The building houses the offices of aides to Vice President Al Gore.
The demonstration was the latest protest aimed at Gore for his role
in a trade dispute, which centers on a South African law designed
to bring cheaper medicines to the country's millions of poor AIDS
victims. (Stephen Crowley/New York Times Photo)
</P>
