<HEADLINE>
WNBA PLAYOFFS AT A GLANCE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By MAC ENGEL 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
WESTERN CONFERENCE NO. 1 HOUSTON COMETS Western Conference Finals
vs. L.A./Sacramento winner beginning at 7:00 p.m Thursday on ESPN
1999 Record: 26-6 Inside the Numbers: 9-0: Houston's record when
scoring 80 or more points. 1999 vs. Los Angeles/Sacramento: 2-2/3-1
Who to Watch: G Cynthia Cooper 22.1 ppg., 5.2 rpg., two-time WNBA
MVP; F Sheryl Swoopes 18.3 ppg., 6.3 rpg., 4.0 apg.; F Tina
Thompson 12.2 ppg, 6.4 rpg.
<TEXT>
<P>
   Why They'll Win the Title: The Comets have arguably the top trio
in the league and an invincibility about them. They force opponents
to adjust their game to match Houston, and few can do it beyond 20
or 30 minutes.
</P>
<P>
   Why They Won't: The Comets don't have a deep bench, but the
psychological effect of Kim Perrot's death will probably be this
team's biggest problem. The guard's death has stung the team's
emotions and overcoming such an obstacle is the hardest thing the
Comets have had to do in three years. Odds to Win Title: 2-1
NO. 3 SACRAMENTO (19-13) at NO. 2 LOS ANGELES (20-12) Series
begins: 8 p.m., Tuesday, ESPN Season series: 2-2 Inside the
Numbers: 1-10: L.A.'s record when opponents score 80 or more
points. 16/27: Times injured Monarchs center Yolanda Griffith led
the team in scoring and rebounding, respectively. Best matchups:
L.A. C Lisa Leslie (15.6 ppg., 7.8 rpg.) vs. C Tangela Smith (8.3
ppg., 3.8 rpg.)
</P>
<P>
   When Griffith suffered a knee injury recently, this became a
cavernous hole for the Monarchs and one L.A. should take full
advantage of.
</P>
<P>
   L.A. G Gordana Grubin (8.9 ppg., 2.8 apg.) vs. G Ticha
Penicheiro (7.3 ppg., 7.1 apg.) If Sacramento is to win, Penicheiro
must dominate this matchup and keep turnovers to a minimum.
</P>
<P>
   Why L.A. Will Win: Leslie and DeLisha Milton averaged a combined
26 points and 12.3 rebounds in the series and that was against
Griffith. Leslie is the game's best offensive rebounder and without
having to play against Griffith, she should take charge.
</P>
<P>
   Why Sacramento Will Win: With Penicheiro and Ruthie
Bolton-Holifield, the Monarchs' backcourt is one of the league's
best. If those two are hitting their jumpers, Sacramento could pull
the upset. L.A. Odds to Win Title: 9-1 Sacramento Odds to Win
Title: 14-1
EASTERN CONFERENCE NO. 1 NEW YORK LIBERTY Eastern Conference Finals
vs. Charlotte/Detroit winner beginning at 7:00 p.m. Friday on
Lifetime 1999 Record: 18-14 Inside the Numbers: 3-10: New York's
record when trailing at the half. 1999 vs.
Detroit/Charlotte:2-2/2-2 Who to Watch: F Vickie Johnson 13.3 ppg.,
4.4 rpg.; C Sue Wicks 7.0 rpg.; F Crystal Robinson 11.7 ppg. Why
They'll Win the Title: The Liberty likely will win the East for the
second time in three years. It has the frontcourt scoring in
Johnson and Wicks and a competent ball handler in Teresa
Weatherspoon.
</P>
<P>
   Why They Won't: The Liberty was one of six teams to defeat
Houston this season and could win the first game of the finals if
they face the Comets. However, Weatherspoon is not the player she
was three years ago and New York doesn't have the perimeter
quickness that the Western Conference playoff teams have. Odds to
Win Title: 14-1
NO. 3 DETROIT SHOCK (15-17) at NO. 2 CHARLOTTE STING (15-17) Series
begins: 6 p.m., Tuesday, ESPN Season Series: 2-2 Inside the
Numbers: .657: Detroit's free-throw percentage in the season-series
against the Sting. 3-7: Charlotte's record over the past 10 games.
Best Matchups: Detroit G Jennifer Azzi (10.8 ppg., 3.8 apg.) vs. G
Dawn Staley (11.5 ppg,. 5.5 apg.)
</P>
<P>
   Of all the first-round matchups, this might be the best. Staley
is one of the best at taking defenders off the dribble and Azzi is
one of the league's top 3-point shooters. As good and durable as
Azzi is, she can't keep up with Staley for 40 minutes.
</P>
<P>
   Detroit C Val Whiting (6.5 ppg., 6.7 rpg.) vs. C Rhonda Mapp
(9.5 ppg., 6.4 rpg.)
</P>
<P>
   Mapp can dominate the game and, if Detroit is winning, Mapp is
rebounding.
</P>
<P>
   Why Detroit Will Win: Since being traded from Utah, F Wendy
Palmer has been a catalyst for Detroit. She's averaged 9.9 points
and 6.4 rebounds and if she starts scoring early from the baseline
and Mapp is rebounding, Charlotte doesn't have the post defense to
stop them.
</P>
<P>
   Why Charlotte Will Win: The Sting have the homecourt advantage
but they are just 8-8 at home. If the interior defense can harass
the Shock's post players into poor shooting and the Staley-Andrea
Stinson combination is on, the Sting can win. Detroit Odds to Win
Title: 50-1 Charlotte Odds to Win Title: 50-1 nn
</P>
</TEXT>
